commitResults.messageTitle: Level-0: Rename main class and add greeting
commitResults.messageBody:
The main class has a default name and no greeting message is displayed.

Rename the main class to Baymax.
Add a greeting message printed to console when the program starts.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-1: Improve chatbot introduction and add echo functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
The program only prints a greeting message and cannot echo user input.

Add echo functionality to echo user input until 'bye' is entered.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-2: Implement add and list functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
User input is echoed but not stored and cannot be displayed

Add a String array of fixed size 100 to store user inputs.
Implement 'list' command to display stored items.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-3: Add Task class and implement mark/unmark functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
User can only add tasks but cannot mark and unmark tasks.

Create Task class to encapsulate a task state.
Implement "mark" and "unmark" commands to update task completion.

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-4: Remove taskId and static id field from Task class
Level-4: Create helper function for command logic
commitResults.messageBody:
Command logic is all in main

Create helper function for command logic
Shift command logic away from main

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-4: Add support for tracking three types of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it
Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time
Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific
date/time

commitResults.messageTitle: Level-4: Implement tracking for the three types of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
Parse input using StringBuilder to extract taskName and other
information
Display all tasks in the correct format
